---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Buy Sound Measurement Equipment"
  description="Curated recommendations for sound level meters and accessories. Budget picks, professional gear, and smartphone alternatives."
>

<article class="section">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <a href="/measure" class="text-brand-600 text-sm font-medium hover:text-brand-800 mb-8 inline-flex items-center gap-1">
      &larr; Back to Measure
    </a>
    <div class="relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden mb-12">
      <img src="/images/hero-measure-close.jpg" alt="" class="w-full h-56 md:h-72 object-cover" />
      <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-gradient-to-t from-brand-950/40 to-transparent"></div>
    </div>

    <div class="text-center mb-12">
      <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 leading-tight mb-4">
        Recommended Equipment
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-earth-500 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
        Curated picks for every budget. Links include Amazon affiliate tags that help fund the platform at no cost to you.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-8">
      <div class="bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-xs bg-brand-100 text-brand-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full font-semibold shrink-0">Budget</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900">Entry-Level Meters ($30&ndash;60)</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-earth-600 mb-6">
          Good for getting indicative readings and understanding relative noise levels. Not suitable for data you plan to present in formal settings, but great for personal awareness and campaign inspiration.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { name: 'BAFX Products Decibel Meter', price: '$30', note: 'Popular entry-level choice. A/C weighted, max/min, data hold.' },
            { name: 'RISEPRO Decibel Meter', price: '$35', note: 'Digital display, fast/slow response. Good for quick checks.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <a href="#" class="block bg-earth-50 rounded-xl p-5 hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-brand-900">{item.name}</h3>
                <span class="text-brand-600 font-bold">{item.price}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">{item.note}</p>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border-2 border-brand-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-xs bg-brand-600 text-white px-3 py-1 rounded-full font-semibold shrink-0">Recommended</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900">Class 2 Meters ($100&ndash;300)</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-earth-600 mb-6">
          The standard for serious advocacy. Class 2 meters meet IEC 61672 standards and produce data suitable for presentation to city councils, HOAs, and other decision-making bodies. These are the same meters in our rental fleet.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { name: 'Reed R8050', price: '$180', note: 'Our rental fleet standard. Class 2, data logging, USB output. Excellent all-around choice.' },
            { name: 'Extech 407730', price: '$150', note: 'Reliable Class 2 meter with A/C weighting. Good battery life. Simple operation.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <a href="#" class="block bg-brand-50 rounded-xl p-5 hover:bg-brand-100 transition-colors border border-brand-200">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-brand-900">{item.name}</h3>
                <span class="text-brand-600 font-bold">{item.price}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">{item.note}</p>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
        <div class="flex items-start gap-3 mb-4">
          <span class="text-xs bg-accent-100 text-accent-700 px-3 py-1 rounded-full font-semibold shrink-0">Professional</span>
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900">Class 1 Meters ($500+)</h2>
        </div>
        <p class="text-earth-600 mb-6">
          For organizers who expect legal scrutiny or need the highest accuracy. Class 1 meters are laboratory-grade and produce data suitable for expert testimony and legal proceedings.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { name: 'Larson Davis 831C', price: '$2,500+', note: 'Industry standard for legal and regulatory use. Overkill for most campaigns.' },
            { name: 'NTi Audio XL2', price: '$1,800+', note: 'Professional audio analyzer with Class 1 certification. Studio-grade.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <a href="#" class="block bg-earth-50 rounded-xl p-5 hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-brand-900">{item.name}</h3>
                <span class="text-accent-600 font-bold">{item.price}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">{item.note}</p>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-4">Smartphone Apps</h2>
        <p class="text-earth-600 mb-6">
          Convenient but less accurate than dedicated meters. Use these for personal awareness and preliminary measurements. Always calibrate before each session.
        </p>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { name: 'NIOSH SLM (iOS)', price: 'Free', note: 'Developed by CDC researchers. The most accurate smartphone app available. iOS only.' },
            { name: 'Decibel X (iOS/Android)', price: 'Free / $4 Pro', note: 'Well-reviewed consumer app. Frequency weighting, data logging in pro version.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <a href="#" class="block bg-earth-50 rounded-xl p-5 hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-brand-900">{item.name}</h3>
                <span class="text-earth-600 font-bold">{item.price}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">{item.note}</p>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
        <p class="text-xs text-earth-400 mt-4">
          Note: Smartphone microphones are not calibrated for precision measurement. Readings can vary by 3&ndash;5 dB from true levels. For data you plan to present formally, use a dedicated meter.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-earth-200 rounded-2xl p-8">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-display font-bold text-brand-900 mb-4">Accessories</h2>
        <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { name: 'Tripod', price: '$15&ndash;25', note: 'Essential for consistent measurements at ear height.' },
            { name: 'Windscreen', price: '$5&ndash;10', note: 'Reduces wind noise. Many meters include one.' },
            { name: 'Laser Distance Measurer', price: '$25&ndash;40', note: 'For accurately measuring distance from the noise source.' },
            { name: 'Calibrator', price: '$100&ndash;200', note: 'For verifying meter accuracy yourself. Not necessary for most users.' },
          ].map(item => (
            <a href="#" class="block bg-earth-50 rounded-xl p-5 hover:bg-brand-50 transition-colors">
              <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-2">
                <h3 class="font-semibold text-brand-900">{item.name}</h3>
                <span class="text-earth-600 font-bold">{item.price}</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-earth-500">{item.note}</p>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 text-center">
      <p class="text-earth-500 text-sm mb-4">
        Links on this page use Amazon Associate affiliate tags. Purchases made through these links help fund the platform.
      </p>
      <a href="/measure/rent" class="btn-secondary">
        Rather rent than buy?
      </a>
    </div>
  </div>
</article>

</Layout>
